I&#39;m glad ye figured out the issue (The FAQ has a little note that 
heritrix has to be first jar when embedding -- maybe I should make it 
more prominent?  See http://crawler.archive.org/faq.html#embedding).

The overlays of the few httpclient classes are so we can wrap the socket 
streams with  recorders to get what actually goes across the line -- 
httpclient does not allow you directly access the socket streams -- and 
code to make the reading of http headers more robust, code that couldn&#39;t 
be added using overrides.

St.Ack


Lars Clausen wrote:

&gt; On Tue, 2005-03-29 at 12:58, Lars Clausen wrote:
&gt; &gt; On Tue, 2005-03-22 at 02:19, stack wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt; Lars Clausen wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; Hi!
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; ...What kinds of events
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; could cause Heritrix to suddenly give up the spirit like that?
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; ....
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;         synchronized (this) {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;             try {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;                 wait(); // wait for the crawl to finish
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;             } catch (InterruptedException e) {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;                 throw new IOFailure(&quot;Heritrix process 
&gt; interrupted&quot;,e);
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;             }
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;         }
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;         logger.fine(&quot;Ending crawl..&quot;);
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     }
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Looks to me as though any thread that sends a notifyAll -- for 
&gt; example,
&gt; &gt; &gt; when the crawler unpauses to start up crawling in 
&gt; HostQueuesFrontier --
&gt; &gt; &gt; will cause your program to exit.  Perhaps add a check that its 
&gt; actually
&gt; &gt; &gt; time to exit.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; No, it&#39;s not that my program exits.  Heritrix decides that it&#39;s done and
&gt; &gt; closes down normally, after which my program is notified of this fact
&gt; &gt; and continues.
&gt;
&gt; Great debugging effort from my coworker found the problem:  We had
&gt; org.apache.commons.httpclient in our classpath before the heritrix jar.
&gt; This stops the crawl after the first page is fully fetched.  I&#39;m
&gt; assuming that the httpclient things in the heritrix jar are workarounds
&gt; for just that.
&gt;
&gt; -Lars
